        <p class="accordion">Do they support iOS and Android?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            Yes, Bassheads come with full support for Android and iOS devices.
            For devices that don’t have a headphone jack, a dongle is required.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="section--heading">Wearables</h2>
    <div class="faqs-section">
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          What to do if I am unable to connect my watch with the phone?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <ul>
            <li>
              Make sure you are using Android 4.4/ IOS 7.0 or above OS version
              in your smartphone.
            </li>
            <li>
              It is necessary to accept and agree to all the terms and
              permissions including the location services also.
            </li>
            <li>
              Make sure you have downloaded boat ProGear app in your smartphone.
            </li>
            <li>
              Do not connect the watch directly with the phone’s Bluetooth, make
              sure you are connecting it via the boat ProGear app.
            </li>
            <li>
              Make sure your Bluetooth is on and try to bind the watch with the
              app. Once the device is discoverable, it will display on the app
              screen, click to connect the device with the app.
            </li>
            <li>
              If you still continue to have binding issues, please restart your
              phone and try again.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">Why is my Bluetooth disconnecting?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <ul>
            <li>
              The operational distance for the Bluetooth is 8-10m. It is ideal
              that phone and watch is in direct contact with each other.
            </li>
            <li>
              If still the Bluetooth is disconnecting, close the app, switch off
              and on the Bluetooth and start the app again.
            </li>
            <li>Make sure the app is running in background always</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          Heart rate monitor is not taking the reading well. What can be the
          issue?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            Hair, tattoo, skin complexion, scaring, wear the watch too lose or
            too tight might affect the readings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          Why does the watch show the step count even when I am not walking?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            Your watch is tracking the movement if your wrist so if you are
            doing something that requires a lot of hand movement then step count
            can be affected.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          Why am I not getting call or message notifications on my watch?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <ul>
            <li>
              Make sure call alert and SNS alert are enabled from the app.
            </li>
            <li>Sync the watch after enabling these features</li>
            <li>Make sure the app is running in background</li>
            <li>
              Even if the notifications are not coming, switch off your phone’s
              Bluetooth and again switch on OR restart your phone
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">How does GPS work in the watch?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            The GPS function can be used only with outdoor sports mode like
            outdoor walk, run, cycle, hiking.
          </p>
          <p>You can record the distance and route with the help of GPS.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">Do they come with different watch faces?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            Yes, all boAt smartwatches come with support for different watch
            faces.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">How much time do they take to charge?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            All boAt smartwatches take between 1.5HRS to 2.5HRS to charge. The
            exact time depends upon each specific model.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          Do they have water resistance? Is it good for long-term outdoor use?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            All boAt smartwatches come with Water & Sweat Resistance technology
            that varies from model to model.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">Can I use other straps?</p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            All boAt smartwatches come with different colour options. Visit
            Storm Strap to get your own.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-block">
        <p class="accordion">
          Do they support notifications for particular apps?
        </p>
        <div class="panel">
          <p>
            Yes, all boAt smartwatches support notification alerts for multiple
            applications.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
